cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.PL 

The paper is focused on the human aspects of software engineering, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper presents a framework for SE human capital and conducts a systematic mapping of existing human aspect studies. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it is the most relevant sub-category. It could also be classified under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.PL (Programming Languages) as these sub-categories are related to the human aspects of software development and could potentially cover some of the topics discussed in the paper.
